==Box office== At the box office, ''Welcome'' opened to a massive response locally, by grossing {{INRConvert|350|m}} on its opening week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=first_week_records |title=Top First Week Earners (First 7 days only)|work=BoxOffice India.com|accessdate=28 May 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081219184647/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=first_week_records|archivedate=19 December 2008}}</ref> Despite facing competition from the popular [[Aamir Khan]]-starrer, ''[[Taare Zameen Par]]'' which was also a huge success, ''Welcome'' grossed {{INRConvert|700|m}} domestically.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=45&nCat=box_office_report |title=Welcome Rules At The Box Office |work=BoxOffice India.com|accessdate=28 May 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080219164657/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=45&nCat=box_office_report|archivedate=19 February 2008}}</ref> It became the second highest-grossing film of 2007, just behind ''[[Om Shanti Om]]''. The worldwide gross was around {{INRConvert|1.22|b}}.<ref name=gross />
==Sequel== A sequel to the film, titled ''[[Welcome Back (film)|Welcome Back]]'' has been released. The sequel features [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]], [[Shruti Haasan]], [[Anil Kapoor]], [[Nana Patekar]] and [[Paresh Rawal]]. Earlier reported to release on 19 December 2014, the project finally released on 4 September 2015.<ref>{{Cite web | title = John gets pricey, pockets Rs 15 cr for Welcome Back | work = India Today | date = 22 April 2013 | accessdate = 2016-05-28 | url = http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/john-gets-pricey-pockets-15-cr-for-welcome-back/1/267066.html}}</ref>
